    "authors": "Chandu M",
    "name": "v1.0 – Resume-Based Job Matching Agent",
    "description": "# 🚀 AI Resume-Based Job Matching Agent\n\nThis workflow automatically finds relevant job opportunities based on a user's resume and sends them directly via email.\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 How It Works\n\n1. User submits:\n\n   * Email address\n   * Resume text\n\n2. AI analyzes the resume and extracts:\n\n   * Skills\n   * Roles\n   * Experience level\n\n3. The workflow:\n\n   * Fetches real-time remote jobs\n   * Matches jobs based on extracted skills\n   * Filters the most relevant opportunities\n\n4. AI generates a short explanation for each job:\n\n   * Why it matches the candidate profile\n\n5. Final output:\n\n   * A single email containing top matched jobs with apply links\n\n---\n\n## 📩 Input Required\n\n* `email` → User email address\n* `resumeText` → Resume content (text format)\n\n---\n\n## 📤 Output\n\n* Curated list of job opportunities\n* Personalized explanation for each job\n* Direct application links sent via email\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Use Cases\n\n* Freshers looking for jobs\n* Developers searching for remote opportunities\n* Automating job discovery workflows\n\n---\n\n## ⚙️ Tech Stack\n\n* n8n (workflow automation)\n* AI model (for resume analysis & explanations)\n* Job APIs (Remotive)\n\n---\n\n## 💡 Notes\n\n* Designed for resume text input (not file parsing)\n* Focused on fresher-friendly job matching\n* Easily extendable with more job sources or daily automation\n\n---\n\nBuilt as part of a real-world AI automation workflow series 🚀\n",
